&lt;h2&gt;FAQs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Tell me more about CDN.net&lt;/b&gt;  
We're owned and operating by OnApp, based out of London, England. CDN.net has support representatives in London, Kuala Lumpur (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/OnApp/status/996693312923930625"&gt;here's a pic of us rock climbing yesterday!&lt;/A&gt;), and Salt Lake City. We launched in 2013, and have been actively helping clients with the web performance problems every day since.

&lt;b&gt;Can you tell me about your network?&lt;/b&gt;  
We source our infrastructure through the OnApp federation, a marketplace of worldwide providers. Through this we're able to purchase bandwidth on a worldwide level, at discount rates. Many premium providers that are LowEndTalk 'favorites', like Clouvider, Total Server Solutions, Innoscale, &amp; SoftLayer contribute to the OnApp federation marketplace. You're able to see our full network of locations we subscribe to here -&gt; https://cdn.net/network/

&lt;b&gt;Do you have PoPs in China?&lt;/b&gt;  
Yes, we do! In fact, we can now help you source your ICP license to ensure your site is visible in China. Contact me at t@cdn.net for more info.

&lt;b&gt;Do you do PAYG CDN?&lt;/b&gt;  
Unfortunately no. We need to sell at a certain price to ensure the cost of support is covered. Likewise, a CDN is most effective when a site has steady traffic. If your site only has a small amount of traffic, I actually suggest focusing on optimizing the code, and images before implementing a CDN.

Any questions? Looking for a specific PoP? I'm flexible - Ping me: t@cdn.net
